Algorithm to Calculate Factorial Using Recursion
1.Start.
2.Define a recursive function Factorial(num):
3.If num = 0 or num = 1, return 1 (base case).
4.Otherwise, return num * Factorial(num - 1).
5.Input a number n from the user.
6.Call the Factorial(n) function and store the result in a variable result.
7.Print the value of result.
8.Stop.

PSEUDOCODE:
START
    FUNCTION Factorial(num)
        IF num = 0 OR num = 1 THEN
            RETURN 1
        ELSE
            RETURN num * Factorial(num - 1)
        ENDIF
    ENDFUNCTION

    INPUT n
    result ← Factorial(n)
    PRINT result
END

FLOWCHART:
A[Start] --> B[Input n]
    B --> C[Call Factorial(n)]
    C --> D[Is n = 0 or 1?]
    D -->|Yes| E[Return 1]
    D -->|No| F[Return n * Factorial(n - 1)]
    F --> C
    E --> G[Store Result]
    G --> H[Print Result]
    H --> I[Stop] 
